commit 686eda3cb4773bb1ffe77cbdef6d0507d8fc2314
Author: Dylan Conway <dylan.conway567@gmail.com>
Date:   2026-04-04T04:57:57Z

    Integrate zig build check into the build system (#28832)
    
    ## Summary
    
    - Exposes `zig build check[-*]` as ninja targets so they automatically
    depend on codegen outputs. Previously `bun run zig:check` could fail if
    codegen was stale — users had to do a full build first.
    - Adds 10 phony targets via a new `emitZigCheck()` in
    `scripts/build/zig.ts`: `zig-check`, `zig-check-debug`, `zig-check-all`,
    `zig-check-all-debug`, and `zig-check-{windows,macos,linux}{,-debug}`.
    Each edge produces a stamp file so ninja can restat/no-op on reruns.
    Gated on `!cfg.ci && cfg.mode !== "cpp-only"`.
    - Updates `zig:check`, `zig:check-all`, `zig:check-windows` in
    `package.json` to invoke the new targets via `bun scripts/build.ts
    --target=zig-<step>`. `watch`/`watch-windows` left alone since they rely
    on `zig build --watch -fincremental`, which ninja can't usefully proxy.
    
    ## Details
    
    - `stream.ts` gains `--stamp=PATH`, which writes an empty file after the
    child exits 0. Lets rules whose commands don't naturally produce an
    output file chain through ninja without shell `&&` tricks (avoids the
    quoting footgun the existing `smoke_test` rule has).
    - Refactored shared bits out of `emitZig()` into `zigBuildArgs()` /
    `zigBuildImplicitInputs()` / `zigBuildOrderOnlyInputs()`. Both obj and
    check emit identical input sets — verified by diffing their ninja edges.
    
    ## Usage
    
    ```
    bun run zig:check                                      # current platform
    bun run zig:check-all                                  # all platforms
    bun scripts/build.ts --target=zig-check-macos-debug    # any variant
    ```
    
    ## Test plan
    
    - [x] `bunx tsc --noEmit -p scripts/build/tsconfig.json` — clean
    - [x] `bun scripts/build.ts --configure-only` — no regression
    - [x] `bun bd` → `bun-zig.o` edge has identical inputs/args vs before
    (diff clean, only `step=obj` vs `step=check` differs)
    - [x] `bun scripts/build.ts --target=zig-check` — codegen runs, then
    `zig build check` succeeds, stamp file created
    - [x] Second run: `ninja: no work to do` (restat works)
    - [x] Touching a `.zig` source retriggers check; zig's own cache reports
    `check cached`
    - [x] `bun scripts/build.ts --target=zig-check-windows` — cross-target
    check succeeds
    - [x] Failure path: zig check exit ≠ 0 does not write/update stamp;
    ninja retries on next run
    - [x] CI gate: `ci-release` profile emits 0 zig-check targets

